<section id="sec.mdsplus_inst">
  <title>MDSplus Installation</title>

  <para><acronym>MDSplus</acronym> libraries gives modules of &sr;'s DataIO
  package the ability to read <acronym>MDSplus</acronym> data from an
  <acronym>MDSplus</acronym> server.  </para>

  <para><acronym>MDSplus</acronym> software is installed from <phrase
  os="linux">an RPM</phrase><phrase os="osx">a disk
  image</phrase><phrase os="irix">its source code</phrase>.</para>
  
  <para os="irix">Building <acronym>MDSplus</acronym> to work properly
  with &sr; is somewaht involved.  Contact Allen Sanderson
  (<email>allen@sci.utah.edu</email>) at the SCI institute for more
  information.</para>

  <section os="linux;osx">
    <title>Installation Recipe</title>

    <para>Follow these instructions to install
    <acronym>MDSplus</acronym>:</para>

    <itemizedlist os="linux">
      <listitem>
	<para>Download the appropriate Linux RPM from the <ulink
	url="http://www.mdsplus.org/software/download.php">MDSplus
	web site.</ulink></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Start a terminal application and become root user by
	  typing the command <command>su -</command>.
	</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Install the RPM, for example:
	  <literallayout>
rpm -ivh mdsplus-redhat9.x-1.6-2.i386.rpm
	  </literallayout>
	  MDSplus is installed in
	  <filename>/usr/local/mdsplus</filename>.
	</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>Type <command>exit</command> to leave the root account.</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

  </section>

  <section>
    <title>MDSplus Configure Options</title>
    <para>For a source code build of &sr;, include the following
    option to &sr;'s <command>configure</command> command to add
    support for MDSplus:
    <literallayout>
--with-mdsplus=/usr/local/mdsplus
    </literallayout>
    </para>
  </section>

</section>